      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera features the M96 3.4L horizontally opposed six-cylinder, delivering linear power delivery through a crisp 6-speed longitudinal transaxle. The chassis retains its communicative feedback thanks to refreshed bushings and a well-sorted multi-link rear suspension setup. Mechanically robust, this example includes a preemptively replaced IMS bearing and an upgraded high-flow water pump to ensure optimal thermal management. While the finish shows honest patina consistent with spirited use, the drivetrain remains tight, the limited-slip differential provides excellent exit traction, and the hydraulic steering rack offers the nuanced feedback characteristic of this analog era.",
